    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Sergei Nikolaevich Kostin<br />
(Born Moscow, 1896; died Moscow, 1968)<br />
Dem'ian Bednyi<br />
(Born Gubovka, 1883; died Moscow, 1945)<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>Battle Signal</em>, TASS No. 0618, December 3, 1942</h3>

    <p>
    Stencil<br />    1930 x 775 mm<br />    The honor of beautiful France has been sullied.<br />
Her culture and life are under fatal threat.<br />
Petain and Laval... How nice the news will be<br />
That France has crushed the treacherous slugs<br />
Under the popular cry: "revenge."<br />
<br />
No, proud France has not long to endure<br />
The evil Fascist captivity: the sky is already aflame,<br />
     Already the sounds are being heard from all directions:<br />
The thunderous roar of growing forces<br />
     And heroic Toulon<br />
Have given the battle signal: “Bring the day of reckoning nearer!"<br />    Ne boltai! Collection, Obj: 205741</p>
        
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

